Customized New Construction Designs by Major Home Builders

When you picture all the options customized homes can offer, it’s easy to get excited about new construction. After all, it is fun to visit different home models and envision a new kitchen filled with natural light or one with granite countertops in your favorite shade. At Pulte Homes, our new homes let you show off your personal style while offering the very best in home design layout and functionality.

We start with an open concept design that provides seamless flow throughout your living spaces. Enjoy effortless entertaining as guests move freely from your kitchen to your living areas. And, with standard sliders, keep the party going outdoors on your covered lanai, perfect for enjoying the natural light and temperate Florida climate. Looking for more innovative spaces? Check out our Everyday Entry®- located just off the garage, this drop zone can help keep your home looking its best by providing storage for shoes and backpacks as you enter your home.

At Pulte Homes, we also want your home to feel unique. That is why we offer curated selections of hardwood floors, granite countertops, and more in a range of styles so you can find a finish that fits your taste. We even offer smart home technology options such as smart locks, thermostats and garage doors—all supported by our built-in wiring -- so you can increase your homes efficiency and enjoy today’s latest technology.

With over 70 years of experience, our team of home builders has helped bring thousands of new dream homes to life.

We Make Buying a New Home Easy

We understand there are several steps you’ll need to take to become a homeowner, and we’re here to help make the homebuying process easier for you. Once you’ve researched home values and visited our model homes in Port St. Lucie, you’ll see that Pulte Homes builds new construction communities in some of the best cities in Florida. This can help you narrow down your choices when you decide to become part of a Pulte Homes community.

After you view new home designs and select the floor plan and personalized features you want in your home, you’ll need to decide which home financing option is best for you. Our Mortgage Learning Center can provide you with more information about why new construction homes are an excellent choice. You’ll learn the benefits of buying new homes for sale as opposed to renting, and the mortgage calculator will help you figure out your monthly payments. You can also create a My Pulte account with an online dashboard to notify you of the documents and tasks you need to complete when you’re ready to purchase your new construction home in Port St. Lucie.

When you decide on the mortgage and amenities you’d like in your home, the building team begins the construction process. You can sign up for Owner’s Entry, which helps you coordinate visits to the construction site to check on the progress of your new construction home. When construction is complete, you’ll inspect your home with your construction manager and receive the keys to your beautiful new home.

Visit a sales center to explore our collection of new construction homes in Port St. Lucie today.

New Construction Homes Near Top Employers & Activities in Port St. Lucie, FL

Residents in Port St. Lucie have a lot to look forward to with new homes close to some of the best attractions in the Treasure Coast area. Beyond the obvious proximity to water-based fun, activities in Port St. Lucie abound. Enjoy a round of golf at the PGA Club at PGA Village or consider catching a minor-league game of the St. Lucie Mets. Looking to relax? Club Med, an all-inclusive resort is nearby. And of course, if you feel the ocean calling, nearby Normandy and Waveland Beach are great places to watch the waves.

When it is time to work, enjoy opportunities at employers in Port St. Lucie like the City of Port St. Lucie, the Cleveland Clinic Martin Health and the St. Lucie Medical Center.

With homes in some of best neighborhoods in Port St. Lucie, Pulte’s new home construction communities let you enjoy all this Treasure Coast city has to offer.

        Your Privacy

        When you visit any website, it may store or retrieve information on your browser, mostly in the form of cookies. This information might be about you, your preferences or your device and is mostly used to make the site work as you expect it to. The information does not usually directly identify you, but it can give you a more personalized web experience. Because we respect your right to privacy, you can choose not to allow some types of cookies. Click on the different category headings to find out more and change our default settings. However, blocking some types of cookies may impact your experience of the site and the services we are able to offer.
        California Consumer Privacy ActPrivacy Policy

        Strictly Necessary Cookies

        Always Active

        These cookies are necessary for the website to function and cannot be switched off in our systems. They are usually only set in response to actions made by you which amount to a request for services, such as setting your privacy preferences, logging in or filling in forms. You can set your browser to block or alert you about these cookies, but some parts of the site will not then work. These cookies do not store any personally identifiable information.

        Non-Necessary Cookies

        California, Colorado, Connecticut, and Virginia residents have certain rights with respect to their data. California Residents. California residents have the right to tell us not to disclose or transfer your Personal Information to a third party in exchange for something of value. This is referred to as the “opt out” or “do not sell or share my info” right. Colorado, Connecticut, and Virginia Residents. Colorado, Connecticut, or Virginia resident, you have the right to opt out of the processing of Personal Data for the purposes of targeted advertising. How to Opt-out. As detailed in our California Privacy Policy [insert link] and our Privacy Policy [insert link], we use certain third party tracking and analytic cookies that may be considered “sales” and “sharing” of personal information. You may exercise your right to opt out of targeted advertising as well as the sale of your personal information by using the toggle switches below to disable tracking and/or analytic cookies. If you opt out we will not be able to offer you personalised ads and will not hand over your personal information to any third parties.

        • Targeting Cookies
          label

          These cookies may be set through our site by our advertising partners. They may be used by those companies to build a profile of your interests and show you relevant adverts on other sites. They do not store directly personal information, but are based on uniquely identifying your browser and internet device. If you do not allow these cookies, you will experience less targeted advertising.

        • Performance Cookies
          label

          These cookies allow us to count visits and traffic sources so we can measure and improve the performance of our site. They help us to know which pages are the most and least popular and see how visitors move around the site. All information these cookies collect is aggregated and therefore anonymous. If you do not allow these cookies we will not know when you have visited our site, and will not be able to monitor its performance.

        • Functional Cookies
          label

          These cookies enable the website to provide enhanced functionality and personalisation. They may be set by us or by third party providers whose services we have added to our pages. If you do not allow these cookies then some or all of these services may not function properly.
